      <section eId="sec_CC-1239">
        <num>CC 1239</num>
        <heading>1239. Â Grandchildren; right to donations made by grandparent during life of parent</heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-1239__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>But gifts made or legacies left to a grandchild by his grandfather or grandmother during the life of his father, are always reputed to be exempt from collation.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-1239__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The father, inheriting from the grandfather, is not liable to collate the gifts or legacies left to his child.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=108588</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
